In your first example, `.next()` works because the collapsible elements are siblings of your links/buttons. In your second example where the links/buttons are wrapped in an `&lt;em&gt;`, they are no longer siblings of the collapsible elements. That&#39;s why .next() no longer works.

In these cases you will have to jump up a level in the node tree by using .parent(). From there you can select the collapsible elements using `.next()`. In your case this should work:

    $(this).parent().next().slideToggle();

